rComments: I absolutely loved his class! He is a very good teacher and I learned so much. His class is a little bit hard at first but if you work hard you will get a good grade. No exams, only research papers.

I am currently sitting in my first ever class with him and he is a certifiable idiot. So confusing. No rubrics, repeats himself without actually clarifying anything, displays everything in Fr even though this is an Eng course, no dates on anything. I don't want to ever come back. NEVER TAKE HIS COURSES.

I liked his lectures, kinda all over the place but if you pay attention and take notes you will learn a lot. No exams, only papers. It was more like a research seminar but it is hard to seek guidance from him... still very good prof. Would take a class with him again

He does not provide dates for anything on the syllabus, so there is usually only a few days notice before a presentation or midterm. He is very unclear with expectations for his essays, even if you go talk with him, which can be confusing. His teaching style is more like a seminar than lecture. Good for immersion students though (uses EN and FR).
He's a really nice professor, but quite confusing at times. Remember to catch on his good mood!
